"Fabian P., Menzel A.","Forests of tomorrow - from a climatologist's viewpoint [Wie sehen die walder von morgen aus - aus der sicht eines klimatologen]",1998,"Forstwissenschaftliches Centralblatt","117","6",,"339","354",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0032469006&partnerID=40&md5=96b339d2099369bc458c31b1251abfae","Lehrst. F. Bioklimatologie I., Forstwissenschaftliche Fak. LMU M., Am Hochanger 13, D-85354 Freising-Weihenstephan, Germany","Fabian, P., Lehrst. F. Bioklimatologie I., Forstwissenschaftliche Fak. LMU M., Am Hochanger 13, D-85354 Freising-Weihenstephan, Germany; Menzel, A., Lehrst. F. Bioklimatologie I., Forstwissenschaftliche Fak. LMU M., Am Hochanger 13, D-85354 Freising-Weihenstephan, Germany","Global climate changes in the course of the past 100 years, that form part of the global environmental changes, are recognizable by a number of indications and can be attributed - to a statistically significant degree - to the anthropogenic greenhouse effect. These climate changes have clear effects on the biosphere: For example, lengthening of the growing season, as shown by indirect and direct observations as well as by phenological models. The forest of tomorrow will be exposed to a number of further climate changes, with likely different consequences for the main tree species.","Forests; Global climate change; Phenology","climate change; forest; global change; phenology",,,,,,"Angell, J., Variations and trends in tropospheric and stratospheric global temperatures 1958-87 (1988) J. Clim., 1, pp. 1296-1313; Bardossy, A., Caspery, H.J., Detection of climate change in Europe by analyzing European atmospheric circulation patterns (1990) Theor. Appl. Climatol., 42, pp. 155-167; Bergmann, J.-H., Zu: Waldbauliche Konsequenzen der Klimaänderung (1997) AFZ / der Wald, 11, pp. 584-586; Bradley, R.S., Precipitation fluctuations over northern hemisphere land areas since the mid-19th century (1987) Science, 237, pp. 171-175; Broecker, W.S., Denton, G.